<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Low rates by the Zona Rosa! The Hotel Segovia Regency is a nice hotel just across the street (Avenue Chapultepec) from the Zona Rosa (Pink Zone). The hotels in the Zona Rosa Cost two or three times as much as the Hotel Segovia even though they are just across the street. It costs about 60.00$ U.S. per night go to their web site and get a 10% discount. I like the Hotel Segovia Regency because the employees make it a career of working here. They are professional, kind, courteous, and friendly. They are their to assist in your every need.In May 2002 there were numerous burglaries from the hotel room safes. I was one of them. The hotel manager and the front desk managers were very helpful in assisting me in contacting the police, moving rooms, and whatever else I needed. I filed the proper police reports and a claim with the hotel's insurance company. After approximately three months the insurance company reimbursed me the cash that was stolen from the safe. Any and all documentation, receipts, letters from witnesses, and photos you can copy and give them is very helpful. Because I use traveler's checks my vacation was not ruined, those were easily reimbursable. My credit cards on the other hand took some time. The credit card companines are not always able to do what they advertise, so beward of high expectations of these companies.You are probably wondering why I am reccomending the Hotel Segovia Regency. I have been staying with them since 1990 and I have stayed with them two times since this loss occurred. The people who work here make it a great hotel. I will continue to stay here.Bad things do happen to good people. So the best advice is to be prepared and have a plan in case something bad, no matter what it is does happen.Note, in Mexico if the crime is not in progress you go to the Police Station and file a report, then they come and investigate it. While it is time consuming this is how it is done.I would rate the rooms as well kept and clean. If you are travelling alone and like spacious spend about $10 more a night and get a double, it is worth the money.The food in the resturant is good. Although there are many fine resturants in Mexico City, an afternoon snack or a late dinner at the hotel resturant will hit the spot. A late night mocha or expresso is always good here, especially with a shot of Khalua. The hotel resturant is open till 11 p.m. The menu offers many choices with some being perpared very well, while some others I did not care for because it is not how I would prepare it.The room service is good, although sometimes the communication gap between my broken Spanish and their broken English does not always produce what I like. If you order cream with your coffee or tea it may be hot cream. Be sure to explain what you want and how you would like it. If it needs to be cold tell them, if you want it plain tell them. And if it is not perfect when it arrives they will fix it to meet your desires.While it is not the newest, nor the most modern the Hotel Segovia is a good place to stay. For those of you who like a nice hotel, central to everything, and with a wonderful staff the Hotel Segovia Regency is the place to stay.George Peter Hanzas! 
<Date>Nov 3, 2002
